ce:section.ce:para:
The Ce0.7Zr0.3O2
                        @Bi2MoO6 heterojunction was produced via the hydrothermal method. 2.5 mmol Bi(NO3)3·5H2O and 0.179 mmol (NH4)6Mo7O24·4H2O were mixed and dispersed into 50 mL of deionized water. The solution was stirred until the compounds completely dispersed into the mixture. Then, the Ce0.7Zr0.3O2 powder were added into the solution (molar ratio Ce:Bi = 0.05:1) and stirred to completely disperse the compound. Successively, the mixture was transferred into a Teflon-lined autoclave with a volume of 80 mL and heated up to 150 °C for 4 h. After it cooled down to room temperature, the solution was centrifuged at 8000 r/min for 5 min. The precipitates were obtained and they were repeatedly washed with deionized water and ethanol, dried at 80 °C for 12 h, and finally ground into a solid light-grey powder labeled as “Ce0.7Zr0.3O2
                        @Bi2MoO6”. In order to compare the characteristics of different compounds, a series of Bi2MoO6 grey powders was synthesized by using the same hydrothermal method but without adding the Ce0.7Zr0.3O2 powder. At this point, 1 g of Ce0.7Zr0.3O2@Bi2MoO6 powder was added into 50 mL of resulted CQD solution. The mixture was stirred at 800 r for 24 h. The water was removed at 80 °C via rotary evaporation and the solid product was dried at 100 °C for 9 h. The dark-grey powder CQDs/Ce0.7Zr0.3O2
                        @Bi2MoO6 was obtained.
